name: Dōnotsura (胴面)
description: Dōnotsura has extremely large facial features displayed on its torso. No stories behind this yōkai, but most likely, it's a play of words. "Dono tsura sagete" is a Japanese idiom to scold a person who looks inappropriately calm when they should be ashamed of something: "How dare you wearing that face" or literally means "lower a face", just like this yōkai.
